value.value: Fused dorsal element constituting the carapace of a turtle shell.

definition.value: The carapace contains a mix of dermal bone and rib cage

value.value: One of a series of bones around the edge of the carapace.
One of eight pairs of plates on the carapace, forming two rows adjacent to the peripheral plates.
One of a series of plates on the dorsal midline of the turtle shell, posterior to the nuchal bone.
One of three plates on the posterior end of the carapace, posterior to the neural plates.
The anteriormost plate of the carapace.
A plate that lies between the posteriormost neural plate and the pygal plate.
A scute that is part of a plastron.
A scute that is part of a carapace.
Enlarged section of perichordal tube that is arranged serially but out of phase with segmental musculature.

label.value: subdivision of organism along main body axis

value.value: A major subdivision of an organism that divides an organism along its main body axis (typically anterio-posterior axis). In vertebrates, this is based on the vertebral column.

A vertebra in the trunk region. For tetrapods, includes lumbar and thoracic vertebrae. Excludes caudal/coccygeal vertebra, which are located posteriorly. In tetrapods this includes thoracic, lumbar and sacral vertebrae, and excludes the cervical vertebrae, which are located anteriorly.
A proximal tarsal bone that articulates with the fibula.
A tarsal bone that connected_to a hindlimb zeugopod skeleton.
An adductor muscle that acts on the jaw. In some species, this is subdivided into segments based on attachment.
A muscle derivative of the mandibular levator that runs from the chondrocranium to the palatoquadrate cartilage. Found in sharks.
A jaw muscle arises near the orbit and tapers as it passes posteriorly to its insertion on the adductor mandibulae. Found in sharks.
Odontoid tissue that is avascular non-mineralized matrix that is deposited by odontoblasts and ameloblasts that are excluded from the matrix.
Skeletal tissue that is hypermineralized and aprismatic and deposited by a combination of ameloblasts and odontoblasts that are excluded from the matrix. Enameloid develops from pre-enameloid tissue.
Each of the two arteries arising from the hypogastric arteries of the fetus and passing throught the umbilical cord to the placenta.
A cardiovascular system that is part of a conceptus.
Portion of midgut after it bends around the superior mesenteric artery.
A hepatic sinusoid that is part of a caudate lobe of liver.
A hepatic sinusoid that is part of a quadrate lobe of liver.
A cardiac valve leaflet that is part of a aortic valve.
A cardiac valve leaflet that is part of a pulmonary valve.

Paired structures in the embryo that represent the final stage of development of the caudal end of the external genitals before sexual differentiation. In both males and females the two swellings merge: in the female, they become the posterior labial commissure; In the male, they become the scrotum.
A genital swelling that is part of a female reproductive system.
A genital swelling that is part of a male reproductive organ.
An embryonic lymph sac that forms at the junction of the future internal jugular/anterior cardinals and subclavian veins.
Anatomical projection that is composed of cartilage tissue.

Paired, cylindrical, and small bones of endochondral origin that lie anteromedial to the anterior end of Meckel's cartilage. The precursors of the mentomeckelian bones are the larval infrarostral cartilages.
An anatomical space that is part of a bone of lower jaw.
An anatomical space that is part of a bone of upper jaw.
A duct connecting the the utricle to the saccule in the membranous labyrinth of the ear.

definition.value: Alternate: leads from the utricle of the internal ear to the endolymphatic duct. - http://medical-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/utriculosaccular+duct. We assume a 3-way connection

value.value: A cranial nerve nucleus that is associated with a vagus nerve.

label.value: dorsal commissural nucleus of spinal cord

value.value: A continuous column of gray matter along the midline in the dorsal gray commissure that sends fibers to the hypogastric nerve.
A neural nucleus that is part of the spinal cord.
